39. Reference Swap
      Swaps the values of two references, or element-wise across literals of collections of references returns 0 if successful, 1 otherwise.
      Syntax x = Reference1 <-> Reference2
      Allowed types for x: qubit, cbit, qnum, qnump, cnum, qstr, qstrs, qstrc, qstre, cstr, ctrs, ctrc, cstre.
      Allowed types for Reference1 & Reference2: any.

      Note: The following blocks of code produce equivalent resulting program states:
            x = [1,2;3,4]                  x = 5
            y = 5                          y = [1,2;3,4] 
            x <-> y

      Note: Element-wise collection literal reference swapping works as such:
            The following blocks of code produce equivalent resulting program states:
            x = [1,2;3,4]                  x = 5
            y = 5                          y = [1,2;3,4] 
            a = "hello"                    a = {1,2,3}
            b = {1,2,3}                    b = "hello"
            {x,a} <-> {y,b}

      Note: The collection literals condition results in the following behaviour:
            The following blocks of code produce equivalent resulting program states:
            x = [1,2;3,4]                  x = [1,2;3,4] 
            y = 5                          y = 5
            a = "hello"                    a = "hello"
            b = {1,2,3}                    b = {1,2,3}
            g = {x,a}                      g = {y,b}
            m = {y,b}                      m = {x,a}
            g <-> m

