      Allowed types for Variables: A list or set of strings containing all of the well-defined variables appearing in the equations, or one such variable as a string.
      Examples:

      x = solvep({"x+1=10"},{"x"}) = solvep("x+1=10","x") = 9 = "x=9" = {"x=9"}
      x = solvep({"x+1=y","y*x=90"},{"x","y"}) = solvep({"x+1=y","y*x=90","y+z=10","z=10-y"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=9, y=10"} = "x=9, y=10"
      x = solvep({"x^2 - 5*x + 6 = 0"},{"x"}) = {"x=2" or "x=3"} = "x=2" or "x=3"
      x = solvep({"x^2 + y^2 = 25", "x + y = 7"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=3, y=4" or "x=4, y=3"} = "x=3, y=4" or "x=4, y=3"

